                                       CHAPTER 1

                                     INTRODUCTION




        RNF is a text formatting program for the Cyber similiar  to  the
        program available on the DECsystem-10.

        RNF accepts (mostly) free-format text which has been put in a  f
        edited  by  BOSS,  and  produces output suitable for a line prin
        typewriter-like terminal device.



        1.1  Features


        RNF does any or all of the following for the user:

         Pagination      RNF automatically breaks text up  into  pages,
                         default numbers them sequentially.

         Fill            Using the margins set by the  user,  RNF  autom
                         "fills"  each  line of the output with as many
                         it  can  hold  without  exceeding  the  right
                         Filling stops at the end of a paragraph, etc.

         Justification   RNF will optionally justify filled lines on the
                         so that the right margin "lines up" evenly.

         Chaptering      RNF will format chapter  titles,  and  number
                         sequentially.

         Sectioning      RNF will format section headers and number sect
                         subsections sequentially.

         Lists           RNF will format and number lists and sublists.

        In addition to the features which are built in, RNF provides an
        use  macro  facility which permits the user to define commands w
        customized to a particular application.
