        1.5  SPACING


        The input to RNF is single spaced.  The output  may  be  single
        double spaced, or triple spaced as the user chooses.

        Spacing is set by the .SP command,.  Once set,  RNF  will  autom
        control  spacing without requiring any further action on the par
        user.  If extra spaces or non-standard spacing is desired, howev
        provides commands for these, too.

        The .CR command provides the equivalent of a carriage return key
        electric typewriter.  The .CR ends the current line and spaces a
        .SP.  That is, if single spacing is selected (.SP 1), the  .CR
        the  carriage"  to the next line; if double spacing is selected
        the .CR leaves a single blank line after the current line,  and
        Throughout  this  manual,  the  action  of  the  .CR is referred
        "return".  Many commands cause a return as a prelude to further

        The .S command causes a return, followed by any number of extra
        .S  and  .S 1  mean the same, i.e., a return and one extra retur
        provides two extra returns, and so on.

        .CR and .S always honor the spacing set by .SP.   The  user  can
        spacing by means of the .BR and .B commands.

        .BR provides a "break"; it returns the carriage and proceeds on
        line,  regardless of spacing.  .B causes any number of blank lin
        the current line.  .B and .B 1 mean the same: break and leave on
        line after the current line.  .B 2 leaves two blank lines, and s

        Thus, the user can create spacing independent text by using only
        .S  commands  for  spacing.   .BR  and .B are used when spacing
        fixed regardless of the .SP setting.



